# Architecture commit messages

When creating git commits for architecture-related work (platform support, structural refactors, cross-cutting system changes), prefix the commit subject with `[arc_name]` where `arc_name` is a short lowercase label for the architecture/feature area.

Format: `[arc_name] <concise commit subject>`

Examples:
- `[windows] Harden filesystem slugs for reserved names`
- `[vault] Retry Git init rename under file locks`
- `[indexer] Drop SQLite connections before Windows cleanup`

Do not use this prefix for trivial one-off fixes unrelated to an architecture area unless asked.
